it.polimi.se2019.limperio.nicotera.italia.events.events_by_server

Class ServerEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.se2019.limperio.nicotera.italia.events.events_by_server.ServerEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    KillshotTrackEvent, MapEvent, PlayerBoardEvent, RequestActionEvent, RequestChooseActionForTerminator, RequestForChooseAWeaponToCatch, RequestInitializationEvent, RequestSelectionSquareForAction, RequestSelectionWeaponToReload, RequestToChooseAnEffect, RequestToChooseAPlayer, RequestToChooseMultiplePlayers, RequestToChooseWeapon, RequestToDiscardPowerUpCard, RequestToDiscardWeaponCard, RequestToPayWithAmmoOrPUCard, RequestToSelectionPlayerToAttackWithTerminator

    public class ServerEvent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Event generated by some components located in server side.

    Represents a kind of general event and is usually adapted to the different situations according to the values of the different boolean attributes.

    The way to understand, by the client, which kind of Event was sent by Server is evaluated the state of the relative boolean attribute. Example: if an event is the type of MapEvent, all the boolean attributes will be false apart isMapEvent.

    Author:
    Pietro L'Imperio
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
